name: PSLV-C58 Launch
description: ISRO's PSLV-C58 has launched XPOSAT Satellite into an Eastward low inclination orbit on January 01, 2024

name: First Spacewalk
description: Aleksey Leonov on Voskhod 2 wade the first space walk on March 18, 1965 which was a mission initiated by the USSR

name: First Human in Space
description: First human to orbit Earth, Yury Gagarin on Vostok 1 on April 12, 1961 by the USSR

name: Space Commission and Department of Space Setup
description: Space Commission and Department of Space set up 01 June 1972

name: First Woman in Space
description: Valentina Tereshkova, first woman in space on Vostok 6 sent by the USSR on June 16, 1963.

name: APPLE Satellite Launch
description: Launched first indigenous, experimental communication satellite; Ariane Passenger Payload Experiment (APPLE) on 19 June 1981

name: First Moon Walk
description: Neil Armstrong was the First human to walk on the Moon on Apollo 11 on July 20, 1969
